OL,3,CFarm worker killed by fire he started
OL,4,Cto keep warm, family say
OL,6,FGrace explains that her brother
OL,7,Freceived a salary of #500 a week, but
OL,8,Fafter accommodation and tax
OL,9,Fdeductions, his take-home pay was #220.
OL,11,FHe posted a photo on social media
OL,12,Fduring freezing temperatures on the
OL,13,Fevening of the incident that would
OL,14,Ftake his life, showing a fire he is
OL,15,Funderstood to have started in a
OL,16,Fwashing machine drum to keep warm.
OL,18,FGrace explains: "I was convincing my
OL,19,Fbrother to stop working abroad, to
OL,20,Fstop working in Jersey because it's
OL,21,Fnot really worth it.
