OL,3,CFarm worker killed by fire he started
OL,4,Cto keep warm, family say
OL,6,F"To any Filipino who is working
OL,7,Fabroad, risking their lives with that
OL,8,Fkind of accommodation, of course they
OL,9,Fhave a high salary compared to the
OL,10,Fvalue of money in the Philippines, but
OL,11,Fit's not worth it compared to their
OL,12,Flives."
OL,14,FGrace says her brother was "the
OL,15,Fsweetest, also the most hard-working,
OL,16,Fjust doing everything to provide for
OL,17,Fhis three daughters".
OL,19,FShe adds: "Now we don't have a man in
OL,20,Four family, so it's really hard for us
OL,21,Fto accept."
